Soldiers opened fire on August 1, 2018 on unarmed demonstrators protesting a delay in the release of the July 2018 election results - fatally shooting six and wounding 35 more. 

The shootings triggered international outrage and undermined the new administration's attempts to break away from the brutality of ex-President Robert Mugabe's rule. Simon Muchemwa reports from Harare… --ChannelAfrica--